comment: The ` QQHom ` homomorphism is a ring homomorphism if the target structure is a field. If the target structure is a division ring, it is a group homomorphism, but not a ring homomorphism, because it does not preserve the ring multiplication operation. (Contributed by Thierry Arnoux, 29-Oct-2017.)
